02/11/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- UN war crimes tribunal chief prosecutor Serge Brammertz will visit Serbia on Wednesday (November 4th), local media reported on Sunday. During his two-day stay, he will meet with President Boris Tadic, Prime Minister Mirko Cvetkovic and officials responsible for the country's co-operation with The Hague. The visit is in connection with Brammertz's report to the UN Security Council, due in December. He visited Bosnia and Herzegovina last week. (Beta, Medjunarodni Radio Srbija - 01/11/09) 
